sammenfassen.  aThe essays in this volume use an interdisciplinary approach to explore the cantata’s rise as a common musical model with a stable basic structure and highly variable areas of application in 18th century Germany. The cantata fostered and accelerated the societal, aesthetic, and cultural process of dynamization embodied in the idea of the “early Enlightenment.”  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCantatasxHistory and criticism. 4aFrühaufklärung. 4aKantate. 4aPoetik. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aCantata.  aearly Enlightenment.  apoetics.1 aBar, Ann Le, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrauschke, Hansjörg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEschenbach, Gunilla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeigel, Julian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirschmann, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirschmann, Wolfgang, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJahn, Bernhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKremer, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaul, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiersemann, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOver, Berthold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPietschmann, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRose, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRose, Dirk, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aScheitler, Irmgard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.lo